{"type": "root", "attrs": {}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Solaris scene viewer"], "extent": [0, 25]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Describes the differences/enhancements in the Solaris viewer compared to the Houdini object/SOP viewer."], "extent": [25, 138]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Viewport options menu"], "extent": [138, 166], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/ui/viewport_menus_anno.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [166, 211]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["In the viewport options menu you can choose the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#delegates", "type": "link", "text": ["render delegate"], "fullpath": "/solaris/view#delegates", "fragment": "#delegates"}, " to use to render each viewport (below the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Set View"]}, " submenu)."], "extent": [211, 356]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["In the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Set View"]}, " submenu you can set a viewport in a split view to ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Image"]}, ", which shows a rendered image of the scene."], "extent": [356, 481]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["The UV viewport type is not available."], "extent": [481, 524]}], "container": true}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Display options"], "extent": [524, 546], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["To open the Display Options, click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "BUTTONS/displayoptions", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/solaris/BUTTONS/displayoptions"}, " button in the display toolbar to the right of the viewport, or move the mouse pointer over the viewport and press ", {"keys": ["D"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, "."], "extent": [546, 738]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Render"]}, " tab in the display options contains ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#delegates", "type": "link", "text": ["render delegate"], "fullpath": "/solaris/view#delegates", "fragment": "#delegates"}, "-specific options."], "extent": [738, 839]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["On the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Guides"]}, " tab, you can show the render time and render stats from the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#delegates", "type": "link", "text": ["render delegate"], "fullpath": "/solaris/view#delegates", "fragment": "#delegates"}, "."], "extent": [839, 951]}], "container": true}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "delegates", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Render delegates"], "extent": [951, 986], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["USD uses a generic rendering interface called ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/solaris/usd#hydra", "type": "link", "text": ["Hydra"], "fullpath": "/solaris/usd#hydra", "fragment": "#hydra"}, ". As long as a third party viewer or renderer implements the Hydra API, Houdini can use it to render the USD stage in the Solaris view."], "extent": [986, 1196]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["By default, you can choose between the native Houdini GL view and the new Karma renderer."], "extent": [1196, 1289]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["If you have other Hydra delegates (for example, Pixar\u2019s RenderMan and Storm GL delegates) installed where Houdini can find them, they will appear in the viewport options menu."], "extent": [1289, 1468], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/ui/viewport_menus_anno.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [1468, 1516]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1516, 1521], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You need to make sure the render delegate is found by the USD plug-in search, using the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["PXR_PLUGINPATH_NAME"]}, " environment variable."], "extent": [1551, 1688]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can also set the environment variable ", {"type": "code", "text": ["TF_DEBUG"]}, " to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["PLUG_*"]}, ", which causes the USD library to print out useful information as it scans for and loads plug-ins."], "extent": [1688, 1857]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "render_delegate_tip"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "title": ["Solaris scene viewer"], "summary": ["Describes the differences/enhancements in the Solaris viewer compared to the Houdini object/SOP viewer."]}